history.content:
You weren't given a conflict form, because your new class doesn't conflict with a class you were enrolled for.

You will be unable to enroll in the class when the waitlist is processed, yes.

There will not be a course conflict form given, because that only shows up when you attempt to enroll in conflicting classes.

Hi, so I am currently on the wait list for CS189, which I added during phase one.  I wasn't totally sure of how I was going to structure my schedule, so I added a discussion time that seemed best and was relatively empty.  I am pretty high on the wait list (position 21) and my discussion still has open seats.  However, during phase two I noticed a class that seemed really interesting which happened to conflict with my current discussion time.  I added the class, but I wasn't given any course conflict form or similar form even though it does conflict with my discussion time... my question is, when the waitlist is processed, will I be unable to enroll in the class because my discussion time conflicts with another class I am currently enrolled in? Is there a way I could preemptively fill out a course conflict form so that I could enroll and then switch discussion sections? Thanks for any help.
history.subject: Conflicting Discussion Time with Another Class
